This is a driver for a media control

WIN32
=====
If the driver is selected for install during the installation it is installed in the system32 folder. 


LINUX/UNIX
==========
The driver should be installed in the system search path. Default installation directory is /usr/local/lib

In the configuration file (/etc/canal.conf) there should be a line as

device1 = "mediactrl,/etc/media.conf,/usr/local/lib/mediactrl.so,64,64,0"

to enable the driver

"mediactrl" - is the driver name(arbitary).
"/etc/media.conf" - configuration file for driver.
"/usr/local/lib/mediactrl.so" - The path to the driver.
"64,64" - Is Driver input/output buffer size.
"0" - Not used at the moment.


